summary: Title: The Cottage Summary: There was a cottage on the hill on the Isle of Man that he loved. It had been beautiful at one point...
body:
Title: The Cottage

Summary: There was a cottage on the hill on the Isle of Man that he loved. It had been beautiful at one point in history. Crisp white siding, a bright red door with roofing to match, large windows and a beautiful garden surrounding the path from the gate to the doorway. He always wanted it to be his one day.

Excerpt:

Dan took him on a tour of the house, giving him a hard hat and the two of them walked in. the hardwood had been all removed, the tile from the kitchen was gone and there was someone with a crowbar taking out the cabinets. Phil felt his heartache in his chest at all the change.

“This was my favourite home in the town growing up,” Phil finally admitted.

Dan’s face lit up, “really?”

Chapter 3

From the beginning

summary: I’m listening to Jimmy on the radio and thinking about how much Dan and Phil are making sure that even when people are upset...
body:
I’m listening to Jimmy on the radio and thinking about how much Dan and Phil are making sure that even when people are upset because there isn’t much content they can’t sustain their insecurities that it’s actually about Dan and Phil because it’s very obvious that Dan and Phil, as a couple, are very much together and living their life as partners. Taking trips home for birthdays and going to see friends together and having their game nights and keeping all their little traditions together alive. 

(The Jimmy part is irrelevant to the post, I know. I just wanted to share anyway.)
